Wind Project Developer
Hangangdaero 416, Namdaemunro 5 gaWork experienceProject Management, Product Management0 - 0Published: 2020-10-22

Your Responsibilities

Due to our dynamic growth, we are expanding our team in Seoul and are currently looking for a Wind Project Developer:

 General/Market
 Maintain an up to date database of renewable energy policy in South Korea;
 Attend industry events and raise BayWa brand awareness in the market;
 Participate in team and company meetings, discussions and workshops and contribute to the regional wind team, providing support where required;

 Green fielding / site searching
 Support with potential new site identification and selection;
 Identification of suitable land for wind energy development, maintaining an up to date Geographical Information System (GIS) database for South Korea;
 Utalising GIS to score and rank high potential sites, carry out the desktop analysis to further qualify the potential and carry out site visits to confirm desktop assumptions;
 Record and report findings of site finding activities;
 Identify and follow up on other potential routes to identify developable new opportunities;

Origination
 Identification of proposed wind/solar projects and potential developer partnerships in South Korea;
 Managing relationships with project stakeholders and following up as required, understanding potential partner requirements and drafting/agreeing key terms of partnership agreements;
 Monitoring key economic drivers for each opportunity, managing internal resources to prepare and submit offers;
 Site visits to confirm commercial points and technical assumptions and gather data;

 Project Management
 Identifying and securing land suitable for wind farm development, monitoring project risk;
 Sourcing suitable inputs for the financial modelling to assess and appraise investment opportunities;
 Support due diligence of new opportunities, both external and internal, to support project investment and acquisition activities. Managing third party contractors and consultants;
 Ensuring project compliance with local regulations and company policy;
 Reporting progress to management and tracking key risks/issues. Maintaining a project technical execution plan.


Your Qualifications
 Third level degree, ideally either in environmental and/or forestry management, town planning, geography or a similar field;
 At least 2-3 years work experience in industry;
 An understanding of the renewable energy sector in South Korea;
 Good relationship management skills, able to easily adapt to a multi-cultural environment and collaborate with international colleagues;
 Fluent in both Korean and English;
 Flexible in approach and time, willing to travel when required and work out of hours when necessary (position is based in BayWa’s Seoul office, but travel is required).


Your Benefits
 Annual salary range KRW 35,000,000 – KRW 60,000,000 depending on experience and abilities Performance bonus Vacations 

We look forward to your application! 

If you have any questions about the job offer, please get in contact with us.
